The paper discusses a method for training neural networks with limited labeled data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a semi-supervised learning method that uses weak supervision and a confidence network to inform the model about the label quality. This method is applicable to a wide range of tasks, including document ranking and sentiment classification, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Based on this information, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
